<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="981" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d981">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">800.515/7–1645: Telegram</note>
                            <head>No. 981<lb/><hi rend="italic">The Director of the Office of
                                    Financial and Development Policy</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CEG1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Collado</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Acting Chief
                                    of the Division of Economic Security Controls</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_OCT1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Oliver</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi></seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-16">July 16, 1945</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><gloss target="#t_Victory1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Victory</hi></gloss>
                                23. For <persName corresp="#p_OCT1">Oliver</persName>
                                <gloss target="#t_ES1">ES</gloss> from <persName corresp="#p_CEG1">Collado</persName>.</p>
                            <p>Please bring us up to date on progress in controlling German external
                                assets especially in Spain since Department’s 5499 of July 6th to
                                    London<note n="1" xml:id="d981fn1"><ref target="frus1945Berlinv01#d383">Document No. 383, printed in
                                        vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi></ref>.</note> and your
                                memorandum of July 7.<note n="2" xml:id="d981fn2"><ref target="frus1945Berlinv01#d384">Document No. 384, printed in
                                        vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi></ref>.</note></p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>